# Repo context shortcut

This scenario launches `sesh cli` from inside the `alpha` repository so the
picker starts with a repo context inferred from `cwd`, then uses `C-r` both on
an unfiltered repo row and on a row selected from a multi-match query.

:bins jj cat
> [!NOTE]
> 'jj', and 'cat' are available.

:t rename-session -t 0 runner (success)
:$ jj git init alpha (exit: 0)
:$ jj describe -R alpha -m "alpha commit" (exit: 0)
:$ jj git init beta (exit: 0)
:$ jj describe -R beta -m "beta commit" (exit: 0)
:$ jj git init gamma (exit: 0)
:$ jj describe -R gamma -m "gamma commit" (exit: 0)
:t new-session -d -s ui "cd alpha && sesh cli -r '../alpha' -r '../beta' -r '../gamma'" (success)
:t resize-window -t ui:0 -x 90 -y 10 (success)
:pane ui:0.0

This snapshot shows the initial picker state with the current repo inferred
from `cwd`.

:snap -d 2s "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{6,8})\b/h"
```terminal
Session:                            │
  5/5                            0/0│
  Current repo: ~/alpha             │
> runner                            │
  ui                                │
  alpha                           ..│
  beta                            ..│
  gamma                           ..│
                                    │
                                    │
```

Move the cursor to the discovered `beta` repo row.

:k down down down
:snap -d 2s "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{6,8})\b/h"
```terminal
Session:                            │@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhh
  5/5                            3/0││  (empty) beta commit
  Current repo: ~/alpha             │◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh
  runner                            │
  ui                                │
  alpha                           ..│
> beta                            ..│
  gamma                           ..│
                                    │
                                    │
```

Press `C-r` to set repo context from the selected row. The header should update
to `beta` while the selected row stays on `beta` after the picker refreshes.

:k C-r
:snap -d 2s "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{6,8})\b/h"
```terminal
Session:                            │@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhh
  5/5                            3/0││  (empty) beta commit
  Current repo: ~/beta              │◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh
  runner                            │
  ui                                │
  alpha                           ..│
> beta                            ..│
  gamma                           ..│
                                    │
                                    │
```

This snapshot applies the query `a`, which still matches multiple repo rows,
moves to `gamma`, and then uses `C-r` to update the current repo from the
filtered list.

:k C-u a down down C-r
:snap -d 2s "/\d{4}-\d{2}-\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{1,2}/t" "/(?:@|○|◆)\s+([a-z]{8})/w" "/\b([0-9a-f]{6,8})\b/h"
```terminal
Session: a                          │@  wwwwwwww (no email set) ttttttttttttttttttt hhhhhh
  3/5                            2/0││  (empty) gamma commit
  Current repo: ~/gamma             │◆  wwwwwwww root() hhhhhhhh
  alpha                           ..│
  ..                           ../be│
> ..                          ../gam│
                                    │
                                    │
                                    │
                                    │
```

